userdoc.notice: The DEX contract stores the reserves for each token pair and provides functions for interacting with them:   1) the view-function `calculateReceiveAmount` for calculating how much      the user will receive in exchange for their tokens   2) the function `trade` for executing a swap. If one of the tokens is the      base token, this will only talk to one reserve. If neither of the      tokens are, then the trade will settle across two reserves.  /// The DEX is ownable, allowing a DEX operator to register new reserves. Once a reserve has been registered, it can't be updated.
